/*An array is a collection of elements of the same data type stored in contiguous memory.

Ques: To find the sum of  elements in array

Declare and initialize the array.

Create a variable (e.g., sum) to store the total.

Use a loop (for, while, or for-each) to traverse the array.

Add each element to the sum.

Display the result.*/

public class SumOfArray {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Step 1: Declare and initialize the array
        int[] numbers = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};

        // Step 2: Initialize sum variable
        int sum = 0;

        // Step 3: Traverse the array using for loop
        for (int i = 0; i < numbers.length; i++) {
            sum += numbers[i];  // Add each element to sum
        }

        // Step 4: Display the result
        System.out.println("Sum of array elements: " + sum);
    }
}
